---
---

<section id="who-its-for" class="py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 bg-[#1c1c27]">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">

    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-white mb-4">Who it's for</h2>
      <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] max-w-xl mx-auto">
        The same local memory layer solves fundamentally different problems depending on where you work.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

      <!-- Compliance-regulated -->
      <article class="bg-[#13131a] border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-2xl p-8 flex flex-col gap-5"
               style="border-color: #67e8f922;">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1">
          <span
            class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0"
            style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #67e8f9, #a78bfa);"
          >
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[#13131a]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 013.598 6 11.955 11.955 0 01 3 10c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.31-.21-2.57-.598-3.75h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.25-8.25-3.286z" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest uppercase text-[#67e8f9]">Compliance-regulated industries</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[#52525b] text-xs font-mono tracking-widest uppercase">HIPAA · ITAR · 21 CFR Part 11 · NERC CIP</p>

        <blockquote class="text-[#f0f0f5] text-lg font-semibold leading-snug border-l-2 border-[#67e8f9] pl-4">
          "Your industry forbids cloud AI for the data you actually need help with."
        </blockquote>

        <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed flex-1">
          Graphnosis makes AI useful inside the air gap. Encrypted on disk, audit trail in the op-log,
          never leaves the device. HIPAA / ITAR / 21 CFR Part 11 / NERC CIP-compatible by
          construction, not by promise.
        </p>

        <a href="/guides/ai-access-controls" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-[#67e8f9] hover:underline font-mono mt-auto">
          How access controls work ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <!-- AI agent builders -->
      <article class="bg-[#13131a] border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-2xl p-8 flex flex-col gap-5"
               style="border-color: #a78bfa22;">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1">
          <span
            class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0"
            style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #a78bfa, #67e8f9);"
          >
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[#13131a]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.75 3.104v5.714a2.25 2.25 0 01-.659 1.591L5 14.5M9.75 3.104c-.251.023-.501.05-.75.082m.75-.082a24.301 24.301 0 014.5 0m0 0v5.714c0 .597.237 1.17.659 1.591L19.8 15.3M14.25 3.104c.251.023.501.05.75.082M19.8 15.3l-1.57.393A9.065 9.065 0 0112 15a9.065 9.065 0 00-6.23-.693L5 14.5m14.8.8l1.402 1.402c1 1 .03 2.798-1.442 2.798H4.24c-1.472 0-2.441-1.798-1.442-2.798L4 15.3" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest uppercase text-[#a78bfa]">AI agent builders</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[#52525b] text-xs font-mono tracking-widest uppercase">Claude agents · n8n · LangChain · custom</p>

        <blockquote class="text-[#f0f0f5] text-lg font-semibold leading-snug border-l-2 border-[#a78bfa] pl-4">
          "Your agents are stateless. Every run starts from zero."
        </blockquote>

        <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed flex-1">
          Graphnosis gives them persistent memory — cross-run, cross-tool, always local.
          Build agents that actually get better over time, on a single user's data,
          without retraining and without sending that data anywhere.
        </p>

        <a href="/job-memory-kits#agents" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-[#a78bfa] hover:underline font-mono mt-auto">
          AI Agent Skills Pack ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <!-- Creative IP owners -->
      <article class="bg-[#13131a] border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-2xl p-8 flex flex-col gap-5"
               style="border-color: #f59e0b22;">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1">
          <span
            class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0"
            style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f59e0b, #a78bfa);"
          >
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[#13131a]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M16.5 10.5V6.75a4.5 4.5 0 10-9 0v3.75m-.75 11.25h10.5a2.25 2.25 0 002.25-2.25v-6.75a2.25 2.25 0 00-2.25-2.25H6.75a2.25 2.25 0 00-2.25 2.25v6.75a2.25 2.25 0 002.25 2.25z" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest uppercase text-[#f59e0b]">Creative & IP owners</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[#52525b] text-xs font-mono tracking-widest uppercase">writers · designers · studios · researchers</p>

        <blockquote class="text-[#f0f0f5] text-lg font-semibold leading-snug border-l-2 border-[#f59e0b] pl-4">
          "Your unreleased work is the next training corpus — unless you make sure it isn't."
        </blockquote>

        <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed flex-1">
          Graphnosis keeps your manuscripts, scripts, designs, and lore on your device.
          Open-source proves it. No leaks, no ingestion, no API key roulette.
          Your creative memory stays yours — and only yours.
        </p>

        <a href="/guides/network-activity" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline font-mono mt-auto">
          What leaves your device ↗
        </a>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
